  "description": "Tier-0 conformance corpus: real canon/hash/cid output, blessed once from the native Rust core (`tm bless`) and frozen. Each case maps 1:1 to a `run_op(op, input)` call; positive cases compare output bytes to `expected`, negatives assert the embedded ErrorCode equals `expect_error` (fail-closed). Hashing is canonicalize-then-hash (I2); the plain `hash_*` preimage is `canonicalize(input)` with NO domain prefix, while `hash_domain_*` binds `CANON_VERSION` + domain. A changed expected byte is a BREAKING corpus release (bump VERSION + CHANGELOG). Determinism: every case is a pure function of its `input` bytes — no op reads ambient time or RNG, so cases carry NO per-case `env` block; signing determinism is supplied INLINE (a fixed `seed_hex` in each signing case's input, fed to `TmSigner::from_seed`), which is why the roadmap's injected `FixedClock`/`VectorCsprng` env is unnecessary here.",
